17:30.333 --> 17:32.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But Christopher
Wray faced few questions about
his experience, and instead

17:32.300 --> 17:35.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a long list of them about
his independence as a
potential FBI chief.

17:35.233 --> 17:37.300 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

17:37.300 --> 17:39.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PATRICK LEAHY (D), Vermont: If
the president asked you to do
something unlawful or unethical,

17:39.733 --> 17:41.233 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
what do you say?

17:41.233 --> 17:43.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHRISTOPHER WRAY: First, I
would try to talk him out of it.

17:43.733 --> 17:46.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And if that failed,
I would resign.

17:46.233 --> 17:51.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: It was one of
many references to the last FBI
director, James Comey, fired

17:51.966 --> 17:54.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
by President Trump.

17:54.333 --> 17:58.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Comey claimed the president
asked him to let go of
investigating former
aide Michael Flynn,

17:59.166 --> 18:00.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
