of warrantless wiretaps, which
he believed were illegal.

18:46.300 --> 18:49.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He was following the lead of
Comey, then the deputy attorney
general, and Robert Mueller,

18:51.466 --> 18:54.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
then the FBI director, and
now the man in charge of the
special Russia investigation.

18:56.866 --> 19:00.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHRISTOPHER WRAY: I view him as
the consummate straight-shooter,
and somebody I have enormous

19:00.300 --> 19:02.300 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
respect for.

19:02.300 --> 19:05.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I would be pleased to
do what I can to support
him in his mission.

19:05.433 --> 19:10.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Wray also
worked on counterterrorism
at the Justice Department,
and was asked today

19:11.033 --> 19:12.566 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
about torture.

19:12.566 --> 19:14.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHRISTOPHER WRAY: My view
is that torture is wrong.

