20:58.533 --> 21:02.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Miles O'Brien has been watching
all this and digging into the
larger questions about the

21:02.700 --> 21:03.933 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
ice shelf.

21:03.933 --> 21:05.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Here's an update to
an earlier report.

21:05.933 --> 21:09.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's part of our weekly segment
on the Leading Edge of science.

21:09.900 --> 21:14.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: This fast-growing
rift in the Antarctica ice
just created one of the largest

21:17.033 --> 21:22.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
icebergs ever recorded,
about the size of Delaware,
weighing more than one trillion

21:23.000 --> 21:24.900 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
tons.

21:24.900 --> 21:27.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
